Protoproposal Chaos33 [rev. 2]

The Industrial Revolution

Be it therefore resolved, that the following Rule be created:

      Certain entities, or classes of entities, may be designated as
      Possessions by the Rules.

      Every entity which is designated as a Possession has an Owner.
      If no other record exists of the Owner of a given Possession,
      its Owner is the Bank.

      Any entity which possesses any Possession, but which does not
      have an Executor nor is already in Probate, shall be placed in
      Probate.

      The Owner of a Possession may transfer the Ownership of that
      Possession to any other entity capable of owning Plots by
      sending a message to the Officer responsible for maintaining the
      record of Ownership of that Possession.  The message shall
      unambiguously identify the Possession to be transferred and the
      entity who is to receive ownership of that Possession.  The
      change of ownership is effective at the time the message is
      sent, unless the message specifies a later time.

Be it therefore resolved, that Rule 896 be amended by deleting the
paragraph reading "When a Player registers, eir Location is the
Welcoming Center." 

Be it therefore resolved, that Rule 1016 be amended by replacing
"Moves to the Stasis Chamber" with "announces that e does so in the
Public Forum", and by replacing "Moves from the Stasis Chamber" with
"announces that e does so in the Public Forum".

Be it therefore resolved, that Rule 1664 be amended by deleting the
words "whose Location is the Beer Hall".

Be it therefore resolved, that Rule 1711 be amended to read,

      A Degree that has been Granted becomes awarded when the
      recipient notifies the Speaker (or eir Delegate, as described
      below) that e accepts the Degree.

      When a Degree is Granted to a recipient who is not a Player, the
      Speaker shall promptly inform the recipient that e has been
      Granted the degree by some means which has a reasonable
      likelihood of reaching the recipient.  The Speaker may Delegate
      this duty to any other willing Player.

Be it further resolved, that Rules 1706, 1707, 1708, and 1709 be
repealed, and further that any and all Locations still remaining in
existence are destroyed.

Be it further resolved, that Rule 1710 be amended to read,

      There shall exist the Office of Cartographor.  The Cartographor
      shall retain the records of Ownership of Plots and of Factories.

      The Official Report of the Cartographor shall contain:
      * the Location and Ownership of every Plot
      * the Placement and Ownership of every Factory

Be it further resolved, that the following Rule be created:

      A Location is an ordered pair of integers.  The first of these
      two integers is the Longitude of that Location, and the second
      is the Latitude.  No Longitude may be less than the Minimum
      Longitude nor greater than the Maximum Longitude.  No Latitude
      may be less than the Minimum Latitude nor greater than the
      Maximum Latitude.  Initially, the Minimum Longitude and Minimum
      Latitude are both 0, and the Maximum Longitude and Maximum
      Latitude are both 10.  Any of these may be changed
      (independently of the others) by the action of any Instrument of
      Power 1 or greater, or by the Cartographor Without Objection,
      but in no case may the Minimum Longitude be greater than the
      Maximum Longitude, nor may the Minimum Latitude be greater than
      the Maximum Latitude.

      For each possible Location (as detailed above) there exists
      exactly one Plot.  Plots are Possessions.

      A Plot may contain Currencies.  For the purposes of the Rules, a
      Plot's Executor is the same as the Executor of its Owner.

Be it further resolved, that the following Rule be created:

      Factories are a class of entities which may be placed upon
      Plots.  At most one Factory may be placed upon a Plot, and every
      Factory is placed on at most one Plot.  The Plot upon which a
      Factory is placed is called its Placement.  

      The Owner of a Factory which is not placed upon a Plot may place
      it upon any Plot which does not already contain a Factory.  The
      Owner of a Factory which is placed upon a Plot may remove it
      from that Plot.  The Owner of a Plot may remove any Factory
      placed upon it.  All of these are accomplished by the Owner of
      the Factory (or the Plot, in the third case) by sending a
      message to the Cartographor unambiguously specifying what is to
      be done.

      Factories are Possessions.  

Be it further resolved, that the following Rule be created:

      Each Factory is of a particular Design, and once created as a
      Factory of that Design cannot be changed to a Factory of another
      type.  

      Every Factory consumes and produces units of Currency according
      to its Design.  The Design for each Factory specifies an input
      of a positive number of units of a Currency, and an output of a
      non-negative number of units of a Currency (which need not be
      distinct from that of the input).

      At the beginning of each Nomic Week, if, in the Plot where a
      Factory is placed, there exist at least as many units of the
      input Currency as called for by that Factory's Design, and that
      Factory is Active, the Factory destroys that many units of the
      input Currency and creates the number of units of the output
      Currency as specified in the Design.  The units of Currency thus
      destroyed are taken from, and the units of Currency thus created
      are added to, the Plot in which the Factory is Placed.

      Any Factory which has, for the entire preceding Nomic Week, been
      Placed in the same Plot, is Active.  All other Factories are
      Idle.

Be it further resolved, that the following Rule be created:

      A Factory with a given Design may only be created by the Mintor
      of the Output Currency called for by that Design. 

      In order to create a Factory, the Mintor of the Output Currency
      called for in that Design must destroy 4 Ergs, specifying that e
      does in a message sent to both the Recordkeepor of Ergs and to
      the Cartographor.  This message must also specify for the
      Cartographor the Design of the Factory thus created.

Be it further resolved, that the following Rule be created:

      The following standard Factory Designs exist:

      Mine:   Input is 1 Erg, output is 3 Ergs.
      House:  Input is 1 Erg, output is 1 P-Note.
      Farm:   Input is 1 Erg, output is 1 VT.
      Church: Input is 1 Erg, output is 0 or more Indulgences, as
      specified elsewhere.

      The Bank may not create any Factory with a Design other than
      those given by this Rule.

      The Bank, upon the request of any entity who also successfully
      transfers 4 Ergs to the Bank for the purpose of making that
      request, shall create a Factory of any of these designs and
      shall transfer ownership of the Factory thus created to the
      entity thus requesting.



